text: Ramsele is a locality in Sollefteå Municipality in Västernorrland County in Sweden. In 2010, 968 people lived there. Since the 1960s the population has been reduced from 1 563 to 968. The locality is located near the Fax River circa 70 kilometers northwest of the town of Sollefteå. == References == Category:Settlements in Vasternorrland County
title: Ramsele
